<dl id="n54107e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54107e">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54107e"> 107(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> n Ayesha <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54107e"><li>FW 284.24 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lg/lexlg.htm#n54107e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lg/l39lg.htm#n54107e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54107e">MS BL 47478-342</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:321 <a name="lad13" href="../../FF/fdra/lda.htm#lgd14">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lg/lgd14.htm#n54107e">Draft: II.2&sect;8.14</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">About this time Mohammed married a second wife, named Sauda, who was the widow of an Abyssinian emigrant. He was also betrothed to <mark>Ayesha</mark>, the daughter of his friend Abu Bakr, but, as she was still very young, the marriage did not take place till three years later. <small> Edith Holland, <a name="EHSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EHSM"><cite title="source">The Story of Mohammed</cite></a> (1914) 70</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
